results.name: Number of series reduced trees with n nodes and integer labeled leaves covering an initial interval of positive integers.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200
program: (PARI) \\ here R(n,k) gives number of colorings with k colors as vector.
R(n,k)={my(v=vector(n)); v[1]=k; for(n=2, #v, v[n] = EulerT(concat(v[1..n-2], [0]))[n-1]); v}
seq(n)={sum(k=1, n, R(n, k)*sum(r=k, n, binomial(r, k)*(-1)^(r-k)))}
results.author: _Andrew Howroyd_, Dec 11 2020
